Use Aranuka
===========

Aranuka has a lot of dependencies to resolve them all it is 
advised to use the maven repository.

You can add the repository of the topic maps lab with adding the following
to your pom.xml:


<repository>
     <id>tmlab</id>
     <url>http://maven.topicmapslab.de/public</url>
</repository>

After that add the dependency:


<dependency>
      <groupId>de.topicmapslab.aranuka</groupId>
      <artifactId>aranuka-connector-tinytim</artifactId>
      <version>1.0.0</version>
      <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>
<dependency>
      <groupId>de.topicmapslab.aranuka</groupId>
      <artifactId>aranuka-runtime</artifactId>
      <version>1.0.0</version>
      <scope>compile</scope>
</dependency>

Change the artifactId of the connector the one you want. You can choose between:

* aranuka-connector-tinytim
* aranuka-connector-ontopia-rdbms
* aranuka-connector-ontopia-memory


Questions?
==========

You can ask any question in the aranuka gougle group:

http://groups.google.com/group/aranuka


Have fun
The Aranuka Team